Wow. Beautiful. Turn the sound on. Take a moment to enjoy this sight. 

Reposted from @twanight The World at Night (TWAN)

© #TWAN_Guest: @Martin_Heck, twanight.org/Guest
Closeup timelapse of comet Neowise from a star-tracker as well as wider, static shots. Location of this video is Eschenlohe, Germany.
🌐 Photographer's web site: www.timestormfilms.net
.
© Music by @RyanTaubert
The title of the track: "A lament for peace - reprise" 
.

node.text: Repost @sergio.rizzuto This shows the importance and impact of isolating yourself as much as possible from those around you. The high majority of people who get the virus will be fine. A bad cold mostly. However, just because you’ll be fine doesn’t mean those around you will be. Your symptoms can lay dormant for days or longer as you spread the virus unknowingly. If you go out and interact with elderly or immune compromised you are literally risking their life and potentially killing him. This is not a joke. Many are saying ‘the flu kills way more’ etc. etc. yes, the flu has killed way more, but it’s been around much longer and has had time to spread. The flu kills less than 1% of its victims. Covid 19 kills nearly 1-4%. If this virus spreads as much as the flu, countless more will die. No more inaccurate comparisons. If this goes unchecked millions will get sick and millions will die. This isn’t a scare tactic. This is math. The numbers don’t lie. Get over being bored in your house for a while. This is temporary and the only way it will work is it people abide by the rules. Don’t go out unless you absolutely have to. Wash your hands. Don’t touch anything or anyone. Wipe down your groceries with anti virals. Cover your mouth if you cough or sneeze. Wear a mask if you’re sick. And do not, under any circumstance, go out if you’re infected or even if you think you’re infected. This is literally life or death for a lot of people and we need to treat it that way. — additionally, the longer this lasts, the more devastating effects it will have on not only ours, but the world’s economy. Yesterday was the 2nd worst day In the market’s history. Ever. In over 100+ years. It continues to tumble. 2008 will look like a cakewalk. At least people could go out and work in 2008. The longer this continues, the longer we are isolated, the longer companies don’t make money. More and more will go out of business. Unemployment will skyrocket, oil wars will continue, homelessness will increase, college funds will be lost. The implications if this goes unchecked will be absolutely devastating. This isn’t just a virus anymore. Take it seriously #covid19
